         <div type="commentary" subtype="frontmatter" xml:space="preserve"><p>These fragments are carefully written in a handsome upright uncial script, probably from the second century (which bears a strong resemblance to the hand of the famous London Bacchylides papyrus, but the formation of the omega is different), though a corrector’s hand has been noted at lines 20 and 34. The fragments appear to have been deliberately cut due to the clear, straight edges. The top margin of Frag 3 is deep, which is consistent with the fine hand, and the verso of each fragment has been left blank. Frag 1 has paragraphoi, which appear to be from the original scribe, however they are conspicuously absent from Frag 3.</p></div>
